aes::semantic(binary_op_in_relation)

  × only union (`|`) is allowed in `let` relations
   ╭─[test.aes:4:16]
 3 │ type user {
 4 │   let member = user - bot;
   ·                ─────┬────
   ·                     ╰── `-` is not allowed here
 5 │ }
   ╰────
  help: `let` defines stored relations as a union of subject types — use `def` for computed permissions with `&` or `-`
